notes: The model failed to identify the target vulnerability. The ground truth describes a critical vulnerability in the YieldMarketRegister contract (function _0x7d6277) where any address can register itself as a market. In the context of the Penpie exploit, this allowed an attacker to register a malicious market that would later be called by the staking contract, enabling a reentrancy attack. The model incorrectly labeled the contract as safe.
